---
title: Jerk Chicken Thighs with a Mango Bell Pepper Salad and Sweet Potato Wedges
description: This chicken is liable to vanish from your plate—what a jerk! No, really, it’s coated in jerk seasoning, otherwise known as Jamaica’s gift to spice lovers everywhere. It’s got that island heat and swagger, so to help keep things cool, we added a crisp and refreshing salad with mango and bell pepper. And to really gild the lily, we’re even throwing in some sweet potato wedges dusted with more of that jerk magic.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/jerk-chicken-thighs-1c95e20d.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/jerk-chicken-thighs-795b2cc4.pdf
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/jerk-chicken-thighs-599f140105346860d1081933
course: main course
author: HelloFresh
time required: 35 minutes
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 590 kcal
  fat: 21 g
  saturated fat: 4 g
  carbohydrates: 69 g
  sugar: 31 g
  protein: 39 g
  fiber: 11 g
  sodium: 250 mg
---

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Cut @sweet potatoes{2} into thin,
¼-inch-thick wedges. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of oil, @jerk seasoning{1%tsp} (save the rest for the next step), and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}, then spread out in an even layer. Roast in oven until tender and lightly crisped, ~{20-25%minutes}, flipping halfway through.

Mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}. Toss @chicken thighs{12%ounce} with a drizzle of oil, 
@jerk seasoning{2%tsp}, garlic, and a large pinch of salt and pepper in a #medium bowl{}. Set aside to marinate.

Peel @mango{1}, then remove flesh from pit; discard pit. Cut into thin slices, then cut slices into skinny matchsticks. Core, seed, and thinly slice @red bell pepper{1}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until charred on the surface and no longer pink in center, ~{4-6%minutes} per side.

Halve and peel @shallot{1}, then mince until you have 1 TBSP. Cut @lime{1} into wedges. Place shallot, @white wine vinegar{2%tbsp}, a squeeze of lime, and @honey{1/4%tsp} (we sent more) in a #small bowl{}. Whisk in a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{5%tsp}. Season with salt and pepper.

Add @arugula{2%ounce}, mango, bell pepper, and as much vinaigrette as you like to a #large bowl{} and toss to coat. Season with salt and pepper. Divide salad between plates, then top with sweet potatoes and chicken. Serve with lime wedges on the side.

> TIP: Slice chicken as needed to create two portions.